The paper deals with a communication system with relay selection strategy and proposes a machine learning-based power allocation scheme. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. The use of machine learning algorithms also suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the study of the performance of the system and the proposed power allocation scheme could also make it relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
